'''''Denko''''' is a 1993 short drama film directed by Guinean film maker [[Mohamed Camara (film director)|Mohamed Camara]]. The story involves [[incest]] between a mother and son.<ref>{{Cite book
  | last = Armes
  | first = Roy
  | authorlink = 
  | coauthors = 
  | title = African filmmaking: north and south of the Sahara
  | publisher = [[Edinburgh University Press]]
  | date = 2006
  | location = 
  | pages = 152
  | url = http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=YhRgqA3aVcEC&pg=PA152#v=onepage&q=&f=false
  | doi = 
  | id = 
  | isbn =0748621245 }}
</ref> The film won the Grand Prix at the [[Clermont-Ferrand International Short Film Festival]],<ref>{{Cite web
  | last = Nesselson
  | first = Lisa
  | authorlink = 
  | coauthors = 
  | title = Clermont-Ferrand Festival of Short Films
  | work = 
  | publisher = FilmFestivals.com
  | date = 2000
  | url = http://www.filmfestivals.com/france/overviews/2000/clermont-ferrand_00.htm
  | format = 
  | doi = 
  | accessdate =5 February 2010 }}
</ref> the award for Best Short film at the [[Fribourg International Film Festival]] and the Golden Danzante award at the [[Huesca Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite web
  | title = 37 Huesca International Film Festival
